File: Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi has been hospitalised, however, his family says it is nothing to be alarmed about. AFP/Rajesh Jantilal JOHANNESBURG - Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi has been discharged from hospital. According to a family statement, Prince Buthelezi was discharged on Tuesday. He was admitted last week for his routine medical examination. READ: Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi hospitalised The 93-year-old is said to be in good health. The IFP founder retired as the leader of the party but remains a member of Parliament. He is also the traditional Prime Minister of the AmaZulu nation.